Pattern 1: Classic Binary Search & Finding Bounds

This pattern is used when the array is sorted.

The goal is to:

Find an element.
Find the first occurrence.
Find the last occurrence.
Find the insertion position.
Find lower/upper bounds.

1. Binary Search (Classic)
Problems
LeetCode 704 - Binary Search
Search in Sorted Array
Intuition
Compare middle element with target.
If equal → return index.
If target is greater → search right half.
Else → search left half.
Java
class Solution {
    public int search(int[] nums, int target) {

        int low = 0;
        int high = nums.length - 1;

        while (low <= high) {

            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

            if (nums[mid] == target)
                return mid;

            else if (nums[mid] < target)
                low = mid + 1;

            else
                high = mid - 1;
        }

        return -1;
    }
}
Complexity
Time: O(log n)
Space: O(1)

2. Search Insert Position (LeetCode 35)
Problem

Return the index if found.

Otherwise return the position where it should be inserted.

Java
class Solution {
    public int searchInsert(int[] nums, int target) {

        int low = 0;
        int high = nums.length - 1;

        while (low <= high) {

            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

            if (nums[mid] == target)
                return mid;

            else if (nums[mid] < target)
                low = mid + 1;

            else
                high = mid - 1;
        }

        return low;
    }
}
